ingredientsDesc:
The DSL-5000 ACTIVE 17a-OH Progesterone Coated-Tube RIA Kit contains sufficient reagents for 100 tubes or 500 tubes.
A. 17a-OH Progesterone Standards:
     One vial, 1 mL labeled A, containing 0 ng/mL and five vials, 0.5 mL each, labeled B-F, containing concentrations of approximately 0.1, 0.5, 1.5, 7.5, and 200 ng/mL (0.30-60.60 nmol/L) 17a-OH progesterone (synthetic) in human serum.
DSL-5000 (500 tubes) contains three sets of Standards.
B. Active 17a-OH Progesterone I-125 Reagent: (YELLOW)
     One bottle, 55 mL, containing < 5 μCi (185 kBq) of I-125-labeled 17a-OH progesterone (synthetic) in a protein-based (BSA) buffer.
DSL-5000 (500 tubes) contains five bottles of Reagent.
C. Anti-17a-OH Progesterone-Coated Tubes: (METALLIC BLUE RIM)
     One hundred plastic tubes with rabbit anti-17a-OH progesterone polyclonal antibody immobilized to the inside wall of each tube.
DSL-5000 (500 tubes) contains five hundred (500) plastic tubes.
